    "body": "It's possible to work-around the errors by using a `[patch]` section in your repo that follows the `[patch]` section in Lighthouse's top-level `Cargo.toml`. For examples of this, see these two external repos:\r\n\r\n- https://github.com/michaelsproul/dummy_builder/blob/main/Cargo.toml\r\n- https://github.com/michaelsproul/eleel/blob/main/Cargo.toml\r\n\r\nLong-term, our aim is to remove the `[patch]` section entirely by publishing our utility crates to crates.io. This will make it easier to use crates from Lighthouse (no more patch section) _and_ the published crates can be used independently. You could even do this now if you are only interested in e.g. `ssz` or `tree_hash`. See this PR: https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/pull/3890",
